---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Agentic DevOps Consulting — htek.dev"
  description="I help organizations control their AI agents. Agent governance, test enforcement architecture, and agentic workflow design — built for machine-speed development."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section id="consulting-hero" class="relative min-h-[85vh] flex items-center bg-bg-void overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[700px] h-[700px] bg-accent-green/8 rounded-full blur-[120px]"></div>
        <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/4 w-[300px] h-[300px] bg-accent-cyan/5 rounded-full blur-[80px]"></div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-[250px] h-[250px] bg-accent-rose/4 rounded-full blur-[80px]"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(52,211,153,0.3) 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(52,211,153,0.3) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 60px 60px;"></div>

      <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-32 pb-20 text-center">
        <span class="inline-block font-mono text-accent-green text-sm tracking-wider mb-6 opacity-80">// consulting</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mb-8 leading-tight">
          I Help Organizations
          <span class="block mt-2 consulting-gradient">Control Their Agents.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12 leading-relaxed">
          AI agents move at machine speed. Without structural governance, they'll ship untested code,
          violate architecture boundaries, and create technical debt faster than any human team ever could.
          I build the enforcement layers that make agent safety structural — not aspirational.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="#book" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent-green/15 border border-accent-green/30 text-accent-green font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-accent-green/25 transition-all">
            Book a Consultation
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 14l-7 7m0 0l-7-7m7 7V3" /></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="/agentic-devops" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-muted hover:text-text-primary font-medium px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors">
            See My Approach →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Services -->
    <section class="fade-in py-24 md:py-32 bg-bg-surface relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/3 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-accent-green/5 rounded-full blur-[100px]"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <span class="inline-block font-mono text-accent-green text-sm tracking-wider mb-4">// what i do</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">What I Do</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg max-w-3xl mb-16">
          Every engagement is hands-on. I don't write slide decks about agent governance — I build the
          hooks, harnesses, and enforcement architecture that make it real in your codebase.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

          <!-- Card 1: Agent Governance -->
          <div class="group bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/20 hover:-translate-y-1">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-5 block">🛡️</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Agent Governance &amp; Control</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-5 leading-relaxed">
              Layered enforcement that makes agents structurally incapable of violating your architecture rules. Instructions are suggestions — enforcement is law.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Enforcement layers: instructions → hooks → gates</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Agent harnesses with budget &amp; tool allowlisting</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Cryptographic approval gates for high-risk operations</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Safe-output contracts that constrain agent writes</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/articles/agent-harnesses-controlling-ai-agents-2026" class="text-accent-green text-sm font-medium hover:underline transition-colors">
              Read: Agent Harnesses →
            </a>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 2: Test Enforcement -->
          <div class="group bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/20 hover:-translate-y-1">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-5 block">🧪</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Test Enforcement Architecture</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-5 leading-relaxed">
              AI-generated tests achieve only 20% mutation scores — 80% of bugs slip through. I build coverage gates that catch what agents miss.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Line-level coverage verification at commit time</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Layer-aware requirements (domain: 90%, infra: 70%)</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Pre-tool-use hooks that block untested code</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Mutation testing to catch false-positive coverage</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/articles/test-enforcement-architecture-ai-agents" class="text-accent-green text-sm font-medium hover:underline transition-colors">
              Read: Test Enforcement Architecture →
            </a>
          </div>

          <!-- Card 3: Agentic Workflows -->
          <div class="group bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/20 hover:-translate-y-1">
            <span class="text-3xl mb-5 block">🔄</span>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary mb-3">Agentic Workflow Design</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mb-5 leading-relaxed">
              CI/CD pipelines designed for agents, not humans. Markdown-defined workflows with governance baked into every step.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2.5 text-sm text-text-muted mb-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> CI/CD pipelines purpose-built for agent velocity</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Hookflow-based pre/post-tool-use enforcement</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Self-healing infrastructure with graduated privileges</li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">▸</span> Human approval gates where they matter most</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/articles/agentic-ops-workflow-framework-for-ai-agents" class="text-accent-green text-sm font-medium hover:underline transition-colors">
              Read: Agentic-Ops Framework →
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Track Record -->
    <section class="fade-in py-24 md:py-32 bg-bg-void">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <span class="inline-block font-mono text-accent-green text-sm tracking-wider mb-4">// track record</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mb-12">Why Work With Me</h2>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">
          <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-accent-green block mb-2">Zero</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm">Production Rollbacks</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted/60 text-xs mt-2">247 agent commits — all with enforced tests</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-accent-green block mb-2">4</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm">Open-Source Agent Tools</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted/60 text-xs mt-2">Harnesses, hookflows, signers, frameworks</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white/[0.02] border border-white/[0.06] backdrop-blur-sm rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
            <span class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-accent-green block mb-2">14+</span>
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm">Articles on Agent Governance</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted/60 text-xs mt-2">Deep technical writing, not thought-piece fluff</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-heading font-semibold text-text-primary mb-4">Read the technical deep-dives</h3>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <a href="/articles/agent-proof-architecture-agentic-devops" class="block group bg-bg-surface border border-border-muted rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/30 hover:-translate-y-0.5">
            <span class="text-text-primary font-heading font-semibold group-hover:text-accent-green transition-colors">Building Agent-Proof Architecture</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-1">Layered enforcement that makes agents structurally safe.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/agent-hooks-controlling-ai-codebase" class="block group bg-bg-surface border border-border-muted rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/30 hover:-translate-y-0.5">
            <span class="text-text-primary font-heading font-semibold group-hover:text-accent-green transition-colors">Agent Hooks: Controlling AI in Your Codebase</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-1">Hook-based enforcement for architecture rules.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/cryptographic-approval-gates-ai-agents" class="block group bg-bg-surface border border-border-muted rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/30 hover:-translate-y-0.5">
            <span class="text-text-primary font-heading font-semibold group-hover:text-accent-green transition-colors">Cryptographic Approval Gates for AI Agents</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-1">Ed25519 signatures for high-risk agent operations.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/agentic-devops-next-evolution-of-shift-left" class="block group bg-bg-surface border border-border-muted rounded-xl p-5 transition-all duration-300 hover:border-accent-green/30 hover:-translate-y-0.5">
            <span class="text-text-primary font-heading font-semibold group-hover:text-accent-green transition-colors">Agentic DevOps: The Next Evolution of Shift Left</span>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-1">DevOps redesigned for agent velocity.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Calendly Booking -->
    <section id="book" class="fade-in py-24 md:py-32 bg-bg-surface relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
        <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-accent-green/5 rounded-full blur-[100px]"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <span class="inline-block font-mono text-accent-green text-sm tracking-wider mb-4">// let's talk</span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-heading font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">
          Let's Talk <span class="consulting-gradient">Agent Governance</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg max-w-2xl mb-10">
          Every engagement starts with understanding your agent landscape. Let's discuss where your
          agents are, where they're going, and how to keep them in line.
        </p>
        <div class="calendly-inline-widget" data-url="https://calendly.com/htekdev/free-consultation?background_color=0a0a0f&text_color=e2e8f0&primary_color=34d399" style="min-width:320px;height:700px;"></div>
        <script is:inline type="text/javascript" src="https://assets.calendly.com/assets/external/widget.js" async></script>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-6">
          Having trouble with the widget? <a href="https://calendly.com/htekdev/free-consultation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent-green hover:underline">Book directly on Calendly →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .consulting-gradient {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #34d399, #58a6ff);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
</style>
